   Angeles to Expand Mall Stake
</HL>
<DATE>
08/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ANG
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   LOS ANGELES -- Angeles Corp. said it reached an agreement
to acquire its joint-venture partner's interest in four
factory-direct shopping malls and a related property
management and development business for an undisclosed price.
   Angeles said it would buy H&amp;W Venture Co.'s interest in
the malls, which have an estimated aggregate value of more
than $70 million. The malls are located in Barstow, Calif.,
Wytheville, Va., Osage Beach, Mo., and Branson, Mo.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Angeles, an investment management concern, said the
acquisition is expected to close in about two weeks.
