</HL>
<DATE>
08/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   MSEL
</CO>
<LP>
   EL SEGUNDO, Calif. -- Softsel Computer Products Inc. said
its shareholders approved a change in the company's name to
Merisel Inc.
   The change, effective immediately, reflects the company's
acquisition in April of Microamerica Inc. Merisel wants to
convey through the name its goal "to combine the best
aspects" of both companies, a spokeswoman said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Merisel is a distributor of microcomputer hardware and
software products to retailers and other sellers to computer
users. About 30% of Merisel's sales are overseas. The company
began over-the-counter trading yesterday under the new symbol
MSEL.
