<HL>
   Initial State Jobless Claims
   Increased in Aug. 11 Week
</HL>
<DATE>
08/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   LABOR
</CO>
<IN>
ECONOMIC NEWS (ECO)
ECONOMIC AND MONETARY INDICATORS (EMI)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Initial claims for regular state
unemployment benefits rose to a seasonally adjusted 366,000
in the week ended Aug. 11 from 341,000 in the previous week,
the Labor Department said.
   The number of people receiving regular state benefits in
the week ended Aug. 4 was a seasonally adjusted 2,445,000, or
2.3% of those covered by unemployment insurance, down from
2,455,000 in the previous week, when the insured unemployment
rate also was 2.3%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Counting all state and federal benefit programs, the
number of people receiving unemployment benefits in the week
ended Aug. 4 fell to 2,369,900 from 2,387,500 a week earlier.
These figures aren't seasonally adjusted.
</TEXT>
