<HL>
   International Brief -- Lend Lease Corp.:
   Australian Firm Posts Rise
   In Annual Operating Profit
</HL>
<DATE>
08/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   A.LLC
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Lend Lease Corp. of Australia, a property and financial
services concern, reported that for its fiscal year ended
June 30, operating profit after taxes rose 18% to 160.5
million Australian dollars (US$131.7 million) from A$135.6
million a year earlier.
   The latest results didn't include any special items. Thus,
earnings rose 2.8% to A$160.5 million from A$156.2 million a
year earlier, when results included a A$20.6 million
extraordinary item. Per-share earnings rose to 95.8
Australian cents from 90.7 cents. The annual dividend,
including special payments, is 70 cents a share, up from 69
cents.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Operating revenue rose 23% to A$1.82 billion from A$1.48
billion.
   Stuart Hornery, Lend Lease chairman, said profit will
increase further in the company's current fiscal year.
</TEXT>
