<HL>
   Money-Fund Assets
   Rose in Latest Week
</HL>
<DATE>
08/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17
</SO>
<IN>
MUTUAL AND MONEY-MARKET FUNDS (FND)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Assets of the nation's 520 money-market
funds rose $6.22 billion to $408 billion in the week ended
Wednesday, according to the Investment Company Institute, a
Washington-based trade association.
   Assets of 253 general-purpose funds rose $2.40 billion to
$142.45 billion, and assets of 105 broker-dealer funds rose
$2.67 billion to $166.07 billion. Assets of 162 institutional
funds rose $1.15 billion to $99.48 billion.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   "Massive asset inflows continued," said Jacob Dreyer, vice
president and chief economist at the institute. Investors
moved money out of equities and bonds and into short-term
products.
   Mutual fund assets for the week ended Aug. 15 were revised
to $401.78 billion. The increase for the week was revised to
$2.54 billion.
